50|$|The {{employee}} who opens the incoming mail should initially compare {{the amount of}} cash received with the amount shown on the <b>remittance</b> <b>advice.</b> If the customer does not return a <b>remittance</b> <b>advice,</b> an employee prepares one. Like the cash register tape, the <b>remittance</b> <b>advice</b> serves as a record of cash initially received.|$|E
