50|$|Financial {{institutions}} and the associations provide payment technology allowing clients to process push pcard payments to the suppliers or send the suppliers a pcard <b>remittance</b> <b>advice.</b> The bridge {{to take advantage of}} the payment technology is pcard supplier enablement. Every supplier must buy into the process and provide <b>remittance</b> <b>advice</b> information, i.e. email address, or other information for push payments (buyer initiated payments).|$|E
50|$|Typically, when paying an invoice, a <b>remittance</b> <b>advice</b> {{will be sent}} to the {{supplier}} to inform them their invoice has been paid.|$|E
